# Docker build context exclusions (slice 037).
#
# The self-host bundle's images build with `context: ../..` (the repo
# root), so without this file `docker build` would ship node_modules/,
# .git/, build artifacts, and any local .env into the build daemon —
# slow, and a credential-leak risk. Keep this list aligned with
# .gitignore's "do not ship" intent.

# Version control
.git/
.github/

# Secrets / local config — never enters a build context
.env
.env.*
!.env.example
*.pem
*.key
*.p12
*.pfx
credentials.json
service-account*.json
.aws/
.ssh/
.gnupg/

# Node
node_modules/
**/node_modules/
.next/
web/.next/
out/
dist/
build/
*.tsbuildinfo
.npm/

# Go build artifacts
bin/
*.out
*.test
coverage.txt

# Python
__pycache__/
*.pyc
.venv/
venv/
.uv/

# Tooling caches
.cache/
.ruff_cache/
.mypy_cache/
.pytest_cache/
.agentdiff/

# Editor / OS
.DS_Store
.idea/
.vscode/
*.swp

# Docs and planning — not needed in any runtime image. The bootstrap
# container bind-mounts migrations/ + controls/ at runtime instead of
# baking them in, so they are not needed in the build context either,
# but they are small and harmless if a future image wants them; left in.
Plans/
